Billy and Saul are smoking on the roof, reclined on deck chairs obscured from the view of the street, and as for other buildings, all they see are windowless brick walls. Billy?s got a bottle of cheap Scotch by his seat, which he?s drinking very slowly, letting Saul take tiny swigs at intervals. ?This device,? he says. ?Who are its buyers? It?s roused a lot of interest.?